<HEADLINE> China Publishes Photo Album on Ten Senior Generals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 29 (Xinhua) -- A ceremony was held here
today to mark the publication of a photo album titled "Ten
Senior Generals in the People's Republic of China."
</P>
<P>
Chinese President Jiang Zemin named the book.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Wannian, vice-chairman of the Central Military Commission,
said that the book, published recently by the Great Wall
Publishing House, is a collection of 417 pictures of the ten
generals' important role in the military events before and after
the founding of New China in 1949.
</P>
<P>
Zhang noted that the generals made great contributions to the
founding of New China, and their powerful desire to fight for
liberation and strong determination to make the communist system
successful deserve to be admired and honored from generation to
generation.
</P>
<P>
Featured in the album are generals Su Yu, Xu Haidong, Huang
Kecheng, Chen Geng, Tan Zheng, Xiao Jinguang, Zhang Yunyi, Luo
Ruiqing, Wang Shusheng, and Xu Guangda. They all received the
honor "senior general" in September 1955.
</P>
<P>
</P>
</TEXT>
