<HEADLINE> Jiang Zemin Stresses Unity (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 29 (Xinhua) -- Party General Secretary Jiang
Zemin said here today that building socialism with Chinese
characteristics is an unprecedented cause that needs to be
supported by the wisdom and power of people of all ethnic groups
across China.
</P>
<P>
Jiang, also Chinese president, was speaking this afternoon at a
forum that invited leaders of the country's non-Communist parties,
the All-China Federation of Industry and Commerce and figures
without party affiliation.
</P>
<P>
The forum, held in the central government compound Zhongnanhai,
was held to mark the success of the 15th CPC National Congress,
which was convened here from September 12 to 18, and the
forthcoming National Day on October 1.
</P>
<P>
Li Peng, Zhu Rongji, Li Ruihuan, Hu Jintao, Wei Jianxing and Li
Lanqing, all Standing Committee members of the Political Bureau of
the new CPC Central Committee elected during the 15th national
Party congress, attended today's forum.
</P>
<P>
"At present, facing the arduous task of seeking new
breakthroughs for the reform and modernization drive, we have to
enhance the unity among people of various ethnic groups across the
country, and enhance the unity between the CPC and all
non-Communist parties, people without party affiliation and any
other patriotic forces," Jiang told participants at the forum.
</P>
<P>
Jiang described the 15th CPC National Congress as "a
significant meeting convened in a critical period of China's
reform, opening-up and modernization drive when there is a need to
summarize the past experience and prepare for the future" The
congress successfully completed all its missions, he added.
</P>
</TEXT>
