<HEADLINE> Jiang Zemin Stresses Unity (3) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The success of the congress was due to the efforts of the whole
Party as well as of all ethic groups of the nation, Jiang
said. During preparations for the meeting, friends now in seats
proposed many good opinions and suggestions, which the Party
latter seriously studied and absorbed, he added.
</P>
<P>
Jiang expressed his thanks to them on behalf of the CPC central
committee.
</P>
<P>
Jiang noted that the United Front is a magic weapon of the
Party. It is the in keeping with the Party's growth that the
patriotic United Front in the new era must be developed.
</P>
<P>
Jiang reiterated the principle of "long-term coexistence,
mutual supervision, treating with each other honestly and sharing
trials and tribulations," which was re-emphasized at the 15th
National Congress of the CPC.
</P>
<P>
The elections of new leaders of the non-Communist Parties are
scheduled for this year, he said, and the new leaders should
adhere to and perpetuate the fine tradition of closely cooperating
with the CPC.
</P>
<P>
Jiang noted that various non-Communist Parties, the All-China
Federation of Commerce and Industry, and personages with non-party
affiliation have often shared views with the CPC, and that they
have offered many good opinions, suggestions and criticisms.
</P>
<P>
All this is essential for making scientific and democratic
decisions, he said, adding that the country will continue to hear
their advice so as to do a better job.
</P>
<P>
He asked them to do more to safeguard the united and stable
political situation, accelerate reform and opening, reinforce the
construction of socialist ethical and cultural progress, build a
democratic and legal system, and push forward the reunification of
the motherland.
</P>
