<HEADLINE> Woodforde Out in China Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 29 (Xinhua) -- World top doubles player Mark
Woodforde of Australia was swept out of the 328,000 U.S. dollars
China Open first round on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Woodforde, second seed here and world No. 31, was ousted 4-6,
6-7 by Kenneth Carlsen of Denmark, who was world No. 91.
</P>
<P>
The Australian attributed his defeat to fatigue. He Arrived in
Beijing Sunday after the Grand Slam Cup in Munich, German and
tried to postpone his match but ATP declined his appeal.
</P>
<P>
Fourth seed Martin Damm of Czech Republic, who once edged
Michael Zhang, went out to Byron Black of Zimbabue 4-6, 4-6 in
another first round match. His compatriot Jiri Novak, sixth seed
lost to Gianluca Pozzi of Italy after three sets.
</P>
<P>
China's top player Xia Jia Ping, ranked 338 in the world, also
failed to reach the second round when he was trounced 6-7, 4-6 by
Mikael Tillstrom of Sweden, a quarter-final loser in the
Australian Open in January.
</P>
<P>
Third-seeded Thomas Johansson of Sweden and his compatriot
fifth seed Magnus Gustafsson moved to the next round by beating
their opponents.
</P>
<P>
Top seed Jim Courier of Ameria, former world number one in the
world, made an easy win over rivals in a doubles match parting
with countryman Alex O'Brien. 
</P>
</TEXT>
