<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-29 16:32 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> PNA Official Protests Against Jewish Settlement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, September 29 (Xinhua) -- The Palestinian Arabs will
not accept Jewish settlements in Ras Al-Amud in East Jerusalem,
said a senior Palestinian official here today.
</P>
<P>
Faisal Husseini, the PNA Cabinet minister for Jerusalem
affairs, made the remark while leading a group of demonstrators to
protest Jewish settlers in the center of Arab neighborhood.
</P>
<P>
He also emphasized that the Palestinians will not accept the so
called compromise agreement reached between the Israeli government
and the American millionaire Irving Moskowitz to replace the
settlers with seminar students.
</P>
<P>
Three Jewish families left on September 18 the two houses in
Ras Al-Amud they occupied four days before after the Israeli
internal compromise. Ten seminar students moved in the same day
who were joined by 10 security men at night.
</P>
<P>
Moskowitz, an American Jew who bankrolled the Jewish settlers,
claimed that he bought two houses from Palestinians long time
ago. The claim is now being challenged by a Palestinian back from
Romania who said he is the owner of one of the houses.
</P>
<P>
The Jewish settlement in Ras Al-Amud triggered Palestinian
protests in East Jerusalem.
</P>
<P>
Peace supporters, including members of the Israeli "Peace Now"
group which opposes Jewish settlement in East Jerusalem, now keep
several tents open in Ras Al-Amud to continue their protest.
</P>
<P>
Husseini said that he would like to sit as long as he can with
the members of "Peace Now" and other protesters because the
Palestinian could never accept Jewish settlers in Ras Al-Amud.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
