<HEADLINE> Zimbabwean Minister Hails Success of CPC Congress </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, September 29 (Xinhua) -- Zimbabwean Minister of State
in the President's Office Cephas Msipa today congratulated the
Communist Party of China (CPC) on successfully holding the
fifteenth national congress.
</P>
<P>
He said the theme of upholding the great banner of Deng
Xiaoping Theory of building socialism with Chinese
characteristics was affirmed.
</P>
<P>
He made the remarks at the opening ceremony of the China's
Tianjin Export Commodities Fair in Harare.
</P>
<P>
"China and Zimbabwe enjoy excellent political and economic
relations. New strides in economic cooperation have been recently
achieved in the area of building materials, metallurgy and
mining," he added.
</P>
<P>
He hoped that the government organs of the two countries will
support and assist private sector enterprises who should seize
this opportunity to increase trade and economic cooperation to
new heights.
</P>
<P>
In his speech, Chinese ambassador to Zimbabwe Liu Guijin said
bilateral trade between China and Zimbabwe has been growing
steadily since the independence of Zimbabwe in 1980 with a marked
increase in the past two years.
</P>
<P>
According to the statistics of the Chinese Customs, the total
volume of trade between the two countries in 1996 increased 67
percent over that of 1995 to 87.31 million U.S. Dollars.
</P>
<P>
For the first half of this year, the volume of trade reached
80.44 million U.S. Dollars, an increase of 41.7 percent over the
same period last year, he said.
</P>
<P>
He hoped that the government departments, enterprises and
business people in both China and Zimbabwe will seize this
historic opportunity and make joint efforts to push the bilateral
trade and economic cooperation to a new height on the basis of
equality and mutual benefit.
</P>
<P>
The 97' China's Tianjin Export Commodities Fair opened this
morning at the Harare Exhibition Park. About 20 companies from
Tianjin, China's third largest city attended the eight-day fair.
</P>
<P>
Their exhibits include machinery, light industrial products,
textiles, garment, medicine and health products, carpets and
chemicals. 
</P>
