<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, September 29 (Xinhua) -- Germany's machinery association
VDMA reported in Frankfurt today that the country's machinery
exports last month continued its boom since June, with foreign
orders up 14 percent compared to August 1996.
</P>
<P>
Total orders for machinery in August were up 11 percent from
the level a year earlier, said VDMA, noting that domestic orders
began picking up, registering an increase of seven percent.
</P>
<P>
In the three-month period from June to August, orders for
German machinery increased by a real 11 percent over the same
period last year, with foreign orders up 16 percent and domestic
orders up 11 percent, according to VDMA.  
