reception of this kind since he took power as a president in
1978.
</P>
<P>
China attaches great importance to the African continent,
especially in comparison with western countries, said Moi, warmly
recalling his three visits to China and the visit in return by
Chinese President Jiang Zemin in May last year.
</P>
<P>
"I note with satisfaction the warm and cordial relations
existing between Kenya and China which form the basis of mutually
beneficial cooperation between our two countries," said Moi,
while calling for closer Sino-Kenya ties.
</P>
<P>
China is "a remarkable country" with which Kenya has been
expanding cooperation projects in trade, technical transfer,
education and culture, he said, urging Chinese business people to
invest more in Kenya directly or through joint ventures.
</P>
<P>
He also expressed his sincere congratulation on the success of
the 15th National Congress of the Communist Party of China
earlier this month and the smooth return of Hong Kong sovereignty
to the motherland on July 1.
</P>
<P>
"At the international level Kenya will continue to support the
policy of `One China' by which we believe the aspirations of the
Chinese people will be fully realized and respected," he noted.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Ambassador to Kenya An Yongyu said China is also "in
firm belief that Sino-Kenyan friendship and cooperation will keep
good momentum and go on with vigorous strides."
</P>
<P>
Moi visited China in 1980, 1988 and 1994. 
