<HEADLINE> Egypt Agrees to Strengthen UN Effectiveness </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, September 29 (Xinhua) -- Egypt agreeed on the
need to reform the United Nations and increase its effectiveness,
its Minister of Foreign Affairs Arme Moussa said here today.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the fifty-second session of the General Assembly,
the foreign minister said it was important to have the UN reform
taken place in conformity with the purposes and principles
enshrined in the Charter and the mandates and terms of reference
it accorded to each of the UN main organs.
</P>
<P>
Moussa said Egypt generally welcomed combining departments with
overlapping activities as well as slashing a number of posts if
the General Assembly so decided.
</P>
<P>
He said Egypt was also in agreement with the
Secretary-General's diagnosis of the real threat facing the UN,
namely the financial problem resulting from the non-payment by
some big powers.
</P>
<P>
He said that his country concurred with the Secretary-General
on the importance of achieving a system-wide integration among the
UN programs that dealt with development.
</P>
<P>
The foreign minister hoped that the General Assembly would
study the Secretary-General's proposals, in particular those
relating to financing the Organization together with the
integration and enhancement its operational activities. 
</P>
