<HEADLINE> Share Prices Rise on Greek Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, September 29 (Xinhua) -- Share prices continued to rise
on the Greek market as the general index closed 1.19 percent
higher at 1,754.67 points today.
</P>
<P>
Trading remained extremely heavy and turnover was 34.3 billion
drachmas (about 1.23 billion U.S. dollars), boosted by a block
trade of 2,700,000 shares in Hellenic cables worth 15 billion
drachmas (about 5.36 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Advancers led decliners by 156 to 72 with another 25 issues
unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Banks rose 0.85 percent, leasing was stable, insurance
increased 3.07 percent, investment jumped 1.50 percent,
industrials were 1.29 percent higher, construction was 0.51
percent up, holding rose 1.13 percent and miscellaneous ended 2.01
percent higher.
</P>
<P>
The parallel market index for small cap companies soared 3.12
percent.
</P>
<P>
Greek bourse has flourished since Athens was awarded the 2004
Olympic Games, but it has also reacted positively to favorable
corporate results and the government's privatization program.
</P>
<P>
Analysts predicted that the market would break the 1.800 level
in the next few weeks. 
</P>
