National Authority President Yasser Arafat, and Israeli Foreign
Minister David Levy are meeting in New York together with Albright
in an effort to work out arrangements for the resumption of
Palestinian-Israeli peace talks.
</P>
<P>
The talks have been stalled since March this year when Israel
broke ground for the building of the controversial Jewish
settlement in Har Homa in Arab East Jerusalem.
</P>
<P>
Jordan signed a peace treaty with Israel in 1994, being the
second in the Arab world after Egypt to have normalized relations
with the Jewish state. It helped mediate the Hebron accord between
Israel and the Palestinians in January, under which Israel should
evacuate from most areas in the West Bank.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. government lauded the kingdom's role in Mideast
peace-making and has granted it some 1.5 billion U.S. dollars in
the forms of debt write-off and economic and military aid.
