<HEADLINE> Yeltsin Accepts Report on Mir Accident Causes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, September 30 (Xinhua) -- Russian President Boris
Yeltsin has accepted a preliminary report by an interdepartmental
commission on causes of the accident on the Mir space station, the
Interfax news agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
Technical and human errors were blamed for the collision of the
unmanned Progress cargo ship with the Mir space station, as well
as for a number of subsequent crises which occurred aboard the
station, Yeltsin's aviation and space adviser Yevgeny Shaposhnikov
said after meeting the president.
</P>
<P>
However, he said, Yeltsin was not inclined to overstate the
crew's error for they have been working in difficult conditions
and accomplished a number of hard tasks prior to the collision.
</P>
<P>
On the whole, the president was satisfied with the current
situation on the Mir space station, Shaposhnikov said. 
