<HEADLINE> People's Daily Editorial Marks National Day (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 30 (Xinhua) -- The People's Daily, China's
leading newspaper, is to publish an editorial in Wednesday's
edition to mark China's National Day on October 1.
</P>
<P>
Headlined "Forge ahead with full confidence and pioneering
spirit," the piece describes the 48th founding anniversary of the
People's Republic of China and the convening of the 15th National
Congress of the Communist Party of China (CPC) as the Chinese
people's "double happiness."
</P>
<P>
It called the year 1997 "a year of great significance in the
history of the People's Republic," for it has witnessed the smooth
return of Hong Kong to the motherland on July 1 and the great
success of the 15th CPC National Congress earlier this month.
</P>
<P>
At present, it said, China's national economy has maintained a
sustained, rapid and healthy growth, while the country's reform
has been carried out in a deep-going way and opening-up drive has
been extending.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, new steps have been taken in promoting the socialist
ethical and cultural progress and building the socialist democracy
and legal system, as well as in army building and expansion of
foreign relations, the article added.
</P>
<P>
"With the people's living standards on the rise steadily, our
country has taken on an extremely vigorous and exciting look," it
noted.
</P>
<P>
Encouraged by the success of the 15th National Party Congress
and guided by the congress' dominant theme, China's reform,
opening-up and socialist modernization drive is bound to open to a
more splendid chapter, the article said.
</P>
</TEXT>
