<HEADLINE> People's Daily Editorial Marks National Day (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
It highly praised the Chinese Communists for having lived up to
the expectations of the Chinese people and accomplishing the job of
summarizing past experience and preparing for the future during
the 15th National Party Congress and the following First Plenum of
the 15th CPC Central Committee.
</P>
<P>
"The congress and plenum have made the strategic decision to
hold high the great banner of Deng Xiaoping Theory for an
all-round advancement of the cause of building socialism with
Chinese characteristics into the 21st century. They also have
elected a cross-century collective leadership with Comrade Jiang
Zemin at the core, which is strong, powerful and enjoys high
prestige among the people," the article said.
</P>
<P>
Guided by Deng Xiaoping Theory and under the leadership of the
Party Central Committee with Jiang Zemin at the core, the article
said, people of all ethnic groups across China are fully confident
that the ultimate goal of economic development will be achieved
and the country will have a brilliant future.
</P>
<P>
It went on to say that the first duty now is to study,
publicize and finally implement the gist of the 15th national
Party congress, unify the thinking of officials and the people
across the country, and combine the forces of all Chinese people
to accomplish various tasks laid down by the Party congress.
</P>
<P>
"We must help everyone in the country to understand what the
15th Party congress means to China's future, as well as to their
own destiny," said the article. "The general public will follow
the truth voluntarily and one-heartedly once they understand it."
</P>
<P>
It also reminded Party organizations at all levels and Party
members across the country that the success of the Party's cause
relies upon the masses of people and their support.
</P>
<P>
"If we want the people to comply with the Party's political
line, principles and policies, we must first trust them, respect
their initiatives, take good care of their livelihood, and always
be ready to help them out of trouble," it said.
</P>
</TEXT>
