<HEADLINE> People's Daily Editorial Marks National Day (3) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Noting that the various tasks put forth by the 15th Party
congress are honorable but arduous, the article said China now
faces both golden opportunities and serious challenges.
</P>
<P>
It urged governments at all levels to carry forward the Party's
fine tradition of hard-work, combine the guidelines of the Party
congress with local realities, and adopt both a creative and
down-to-earth style of work.
</P>
<P>
"We should abandon empty talk and formalities and emphasize
practical work and effective results, ensuring that the principles
and policies adopted by the Party congress are implemented in
every region, department and unit," it suggested.
</P>
<P>
The editorial finally noted that historical experience in
founding and developing New China has proved that both the future
and destiny of the country are closely related to the Communist
Party of China.
</P>
<P>
"Whenever the Communist Party adopted the correct line,
principles and policies, our country enjoyed prosperity and
promising prospects," it commented.
</P>
<P>
It added that the 15th CPC National Congress has brought a
brighter future to socialist China by offering a glorious guiding
banner, setting a clear development goal and making the Party
stronger than ever.
</P>
<P>
"Let's hold high the great banner of Deng Xiaoping Theory,
rally more closely around the Party Central Committee with Jiang
Zemin at the core, work hard and forge ahead with pioneering
spirit, to score more victories in the great cause of building
socialism with Chinese characteristics," the editorial concluded.
</P>
</TEXT>
