<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Russian Army Needs To Be Updated: Defense Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, September 30 (Xinhua) -- Russia needs to increase its
spending in order to develop new technology to create and produce
modern armaments to equip its army, Russian Defense Minister Igor
Sergeyev said today.
</P>
<P>
Addressing a group of people from literary and art circles,
Sergeyev said the Russian army would stop buying military
hardware of old models and would gradually start to equip itself
with new armaments and hardware in 2001, the Itar-Tass news agency
reported.
</P>
<P>
The defense minister warned that if Russia "does not provide
modern armaments and military hardware for its army, it will
become an exhibition army."
</P>
<P>
The danger of the outbreak of a large-scale war would grow
following the depletion of energy resources in the world. In
preparation for that, the Russian Army "should be strong and
should possess high combat efficiency," Sergeyev said.
</P>
<P>
As for the military reform, he said the Russian army planned to
reduce its command structures in 1997-1998. 
</P>
</TEXT>
