<HEADLINE> Bank of Montreal Opens Branch in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 30 (Xinhua) -- Bank of Montreal (BOM), one
of the top 10 banks in North America, opened its second branch in
China, the Beijing Branch, in the country's capital today.
</P>
<P>
"This is the latest proof of our confidence in China's economic
growth," Matthew W. Barret, chairman and CEO of the bank, said at
the opening ceremony here today.
</P>
<P>
The bank also signed a memorandum of understanding today with
the Industrial and Commercial Bank of China (ICBC) to increase
cooperation on the basis of mutual benefits.
</P>
<P>
BOM's Beijing Branch will help develop China's trade and
investment ties with Canada, as well as the rest of North America,
Barret said.
</P>
<P>
Bank of Montreal has total assets of 203 billion Canadian
dollars. Earlier, the BOM set up its first China branch in
Guangzhou, capital of the southern Guangdong Province.
</P>
<P>
The BOM Beijing Branch has hired 25 employees, and has been
approved to invest 12.3 million US dollars in local businesses.
</P>
</TEXT>
