<HEADLINE> Large Tonnage Port Built in Fujian Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XIAMEN, September 30 (Xinhua) -- The nearest port to Taiwan in
east China's interior area, Weitou port in Jinjing town of
Jinjiang city in Fujian Province, started operation today.
</P>
<P>
The strait between Weitou Village and Jinmen Island of Taiwan,
which covers a distance of only 5.6 knots, has always been a vital
waterway connecting the two areas.
</P>
<P>
With a total investment of 144 million yuan (17 million US
dollars), the new port has multiple uses, including a 3,000-ton
berth for working ships and some supplementary facilities.
</P>
<P>
The purpose of the port, which went under construction in
January 1996, is to benefit the non-governmental trading between
Taiwan and China's mainland. 
</P>
</TEXT>
