<HEADLINE> Sino-Canadian School Opens in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 30 (Xinhua) -- A Sino-Canadian school, with
more than 200 students and teachers from both China and
Canada, opened in Beijing today.
</P>
<P>
The school, jointly sponsored by the Experimental School of
Beijing Normal University, the Education Department of New
Brunswick in Canada and AKD International Inc., combines high
school education and professional training and aims at cultivating
international-standard professional personnel for the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
It will incorporate the best of both Chinese and Canadian
teaching methods, according to the school authorities.
</P>
<P>
The school is expected to have 1,000 students by the year
2000.  
