maintain its position as a world center in finance, trade,
shipping, tourism and information.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong could also become a new high-tech center in the world
through expansion of cooperation with interior areas in technology
and education, he noted.
</P>
<P>
Cheng said all group members, comprising presidents of Hong
Kong's universities and high schools, are pleased to attend the
National Day activities taking place in the wake of Hong Kong's
return.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, he said, Hong Kong hopes to increase its exchanges
and cooperation with interior areas in education.
</P>
<P>
Cheng and his party arrived here Monday at the invitation of
the Hong Kong and Macao Affairs Office of the State Council.
</P>
