<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Beijing University Opens Deng Xiaoping Theory Course </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 30 (Xinhua) -- Beijing University in the
Chinese capital officially opened a course on Deng Xiaoping
Theory today.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai, a stop during Deng's famous southern tour in 1992
when he gave speeches on accelerating reforms and opening-up in
China, opened the course in 1994, the first Chinese city to do so.
</P>
<P>
At 7 a.m., classroom 109 of Beijing University was filled
with enthusiastic students. Some teachers also stopped by to hear
today's lecture by Wu Shuqing, an economist and former president
of the university, who talked about the primary stage of socialism
and the policies of the Chinese Communist Party.
</P>
<P>
Combining theory and true life examples, Wu's lecture received
laughter and applause. When the lecture was over, many students were
reluctant to leave, raising questions about public ownership to Wu.
</P>
<P>
"What a wonderful course. It quenched my thirst," said Chen
Wei, a student majoring in political and administrative
management.
</P>
<P>
"I've found answers to many of my questions," said Zhang Biao,
another student. "And I am full of confidence in my country's
future."
</P>
<P>
Chen Zhan'an, head of the Marxism College of the university,
told Xinhua that five departments have included Deng Xiaoping
Theory in their curriculum.
</P>
<P>
The students were also organized to study the report of the
15th National Congress of the Communist Party of China, which set
Deng Xiaoping Theory as the guideline for the whole Party and the
nation.
</P>
<P>
"My purpose is to make Deng Xiaoping Theory understandable
among the students, and let it solve real problems," professor Wu
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
