<HEADLINE> China Opens Eight More Counties to Foreigners </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 30 (Xinhua) -- The State Council announced
here today that it has approved the opening-up of eight more
counties and county-level cities to foreigners, bringing the total
number of opened-up counties in China to 1,314.
</P>
<P>
The locales to be newly opened include Houma City of north
China's Shanxi Province, Linhe City, Dengkou County, Wuyuan
County, Hanggin Rear Banner and Urad Front Banner of north China's
Inner Mongolia Autonomous Region, and Gangca County and Minhe Hui
and Tu Nationalities Autonomous County of northwest China's
Qinghai Province.
</P>
<P>
Chinese laws permit foreigners holding valid visas or residency
permits to travel to those regions without applying for any travel
documents in advance. 
