<HEADLINE> Beijing Reception Marks 48th National Day (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 30 (Xinhua) -- Premier Li Peng today hailed
the recently-concluded 15th National Congress of the Chinese
Communist Party as a great milestone in the history of the Party
and the country, saying that the event is bound to have a
far-reaching impact on China's future development.
</P>
<P>
Li Peng made the remarks at a grand reception he hosted in the
Great Hall of the People this evening to mark the 48th anniversary
of the founding of the People's Republic of China.
</P>
<P>
Chinese leaders Jiang Zemin, Qiao Shi, Zhu Rongji, Li Ruihuan,
Liu Huaqing, Hu Jintao, Wei Jianxing, Li Lanqing and Rong Yiren
were among those present at the reception.
</P>
<P>
"The year 1998 will be an important year carrying out the
guidelines of the congress and implementing the Ninth Five-Year
Plan (1996-2000) in a comprehensive way," Li said while proposing
a toast.
</P>
<P>
China shall continue to implement the policies and guidelines
set forth by the Party Central Committee by conscientiously
promoting economic structural changes and a shift in the mode of
economic growth, maintaining the sustained, rapid and sound growth
of the national economy, and bringing about all-around social
progress, he said.
</P>
<P>
The premier noted that measures should be taken to strengthen
agriculture so as to have an even better harvest next year.
</P>
<P>
As the reform of state-owned enterprises is a priority of
China's economic restructuring at present and in the days ahead,
he said, greater efforts should be made in this regard.
</P>
<P>
To do this well, he added, leaders should have a strong sense
of the policy, proceed from the specific conditions of different
localities, act in compliance with the law governing economic
development, respect the will of the people and actively advance
the reform in a down-to-earth manner while constantly summing up
the country's experience.
</P>
<P>
Financial work should be managed well and precautions should be
taken against financial risks by further intensifying financial
restructuring, he said.
</P>
<P>
"We shall further improve socialist democracy and legal system
and actively advance institutional reform. And we shall further
intensity our efforts to build a diligent and honest
administration and fight against corruption, and take effective
and comprehensive measures for overall control of public
security," the premier emphasized.
</P>
<P>
Governments and leading cadres at all levels should do even
more to care for the well-being of the people, and especially help
the needy workers and peasants to overcome their difficulties in
making a living, he noted.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
