<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Beijing Reception Marks 48th National Day (3) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Marked progress has been made in raising the productive forces,
increasing the overall national strength and improving the people's
livelihoods, he said.
</P>
<P>
This year, China's economy has maintained a good momentum of
growth, with price increases continuing to drop. Despite severe
drought in quite a few areas this autumn, this year's harvest
looks promising on the whole, Li noted.
</P>
<P>
He continued that the reform of state-owned enterprises is in
full swing, which has resulted in improved economic returns and
some positive changes.
</P>
<P>
"Our economic cooperation with the outside world has continued
to expand while the import and export trade has kept growing," he
noted, adding that China's foreign exchange reserve has also
increased by a wide margin.
</P>
<P>
There is an amply supply of commodities in the urban and rural
markets and the people's quality of life has continued to improve,
he said, noting that new achievements have been scored in the
areas of science and technology, education, culture, public health
and sports as well as in the building of the nation's defense
system.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, great efforts have been made to promote socialist
ethical and cultural progress and strengthen the socialist
democracy and legal system. China's diplomacy has also made
progress and the country's international status has been further
enhanced with each passing day, he acknowledged.
</P>
<P>
The entire country is now a land of prosperity with economic
growth, political stability, ethnic harmony, social progress and
people living and working in peace and contentment, the premier
said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970930.0099 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Beijing Reception Marks 48th National Day (4) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
"Though we have scored tremendous progress, we should always
soberly keep in mind that China is still a developing country in
the primary stage of socialism. With uneven regional economic
development, there are still more than 50 million people without
adequate supply of food and clothing," Li said.
</P>
<P>
At present, he acknowledged, with the structural readjustment
of the economy and the further advancement of the reform of the
state-owned enterprises, the task of re-employment for laid-off
workers is becoming tough and public security in some areas is
still not satisfactory.
</P>
<P>
Certain unhealthy phenomena like corruption continue to pose
serious problems, he said, adding that "we must face up to the
problems on our way ahead and are working in earnest to solve
them."
</P>
<P>
On the international situation, Li said, the world is rapidly
moving in the direction of multi-polarization, which has become an
undeniable historical trend.
</P>
<P>
The development towards multipolarity serves the interest of
peace and development and is conducive to the establishment of an
equitable and rational new international political and economic
order and the maintenance of the legitimate rights and interests
of all countries, Li added.
</P>
<P>
Li went on to say that the Chinese government will unswervingly
pursue an independent foreign policy of peace, oppose hegemonism,
safeguard world peace, and promote the cause for human progress.
</P>
<P>
"We are ready to establish and develop, on the basis of the
Five Principles of Peaceful Co-existence, friendly relations and
cooperation with all countries in the world, and together with the
people throughout the world work hard for the establishment of a
new world of peace, security, cooperation and prosperity," the
Chinese premier concluded. 
</P>
</TEXT>
