</P>
<P>
ABU DHABI -- The Cabinet of the United Arab Emirates (UAE) has
approved a draft law putting a ceiling on wedding expenses in the
Gulf country, official newspaper Emirates News reported today.
</P>
<P>
The draft law, which sets dowries at a maximum of 20,000
dirhams (some 5,500 U.S. dollars) and limiting wedding parties to
one day, is aimed at curbing soaring wedding expenses which have
become a heavy burden to the UAE's youth.
</P>
<P>
The draft law which also sets a 30,000 dirhams (about 8,200
dollars) limit on divorce compensation is part of the government's
effort to promote marriage among its nationals. (UAE-Law-Wedding)
</P>
