<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> France Condemns Foreign Intervention in Iraqi Territory </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, September 30 (Xinhua) -- France today condemned what it
called ``foreign intervention in Iraqi territory,'' after Iraq
accused Iranian planes of bombing two military bases of an Iranian
opposition group inside Iraq on Monday.
</P>
<P>
French Foreign Ministry spokesman Jacques Rummelhardt reaffirmed
France's support to Iraq's efforts to keep its territorial
integrity, and called on Turkey to immediately withdraw its troops
from northern Iraq.
</P>
<P>
Backed by the United States, Turkey has been repeatedly launching
military operations in northern Iraq against the Kurdistan Workers'
Party (PKK).
</P>
<P>
``We are worried about the foreign military intervention in Iraqi
territory. It is in effect a fragile region where foreign operations
can have grave destabilizing effect,'' said Rummelhardt.
</P>
<P>
He also expressed worry over the safety of the civilians in
northern Iraq, now frequently subjected to military actions from
troops of Iraq, Turkey as well as Kurdish groups.
</P>
<P>
``We are equally worried about the consequences (of these
military actions) upon civil population (in the region), who have
already been severely tested. France is particularly attached to the
sovereignty of the states and it reproaches all violation of this
principle,'' said the spokesman. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
