Americans, extending increasingly to racial and ethnic minorities
and reaching farther down the economic ladder as the nation's
economic recovery moves briskly through its sixth year, a number
of reports indicate.
</P>
<P>
-- Delighted at a 2 billion U.S. dollars contract signed
between a French oil company and Iran, Prime Minister Lionel
Jospin of France rejected an American law that claims the power to
impose sanctions even on non-American companies investing more
than 40 million U.S. dollars in Iran and Libya.
</P>
