<HEADLINE> Overseas Chinese Gather at Tian'anmen Rostrum </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 30 (Xinhua) -- More than 1,000 compatriots
from the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region, Taiwan and
Macao, overseas Chinese and nationals residing abroad mounted the
Tian'anmen Rostrum yesterday after attending a national day
reception in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
At the rostrum, which overlooked a sea of flowers,
lanterns and an exuberant crowd, they talked about the great
development and bright future of the motherland.
</P>
<P>
"I am very proud of the prosperous motherland," said a Chinese
from Germany, who brought his wife and child to Beijing. "I came
back to China every a few years, and each time I got here I was
surprised by the big changes I saw."
</P>
<P>
A 70-year-old Taiwan resident, whose family has its origin
in east China's Fujian Province, said, "I believe our motherland
will finally achieve its unification."
</P>
<P>
He added that the "two Chinas" and "one China, one Taiwan"
principles are doomed to fail.
</P>
<P>
"My friends and I are all against 'Taiwan independence'," said
the man, who had just listened to Vice-Premier Qian Qichen's
speech at the reception, in which Qian said that the Chinese
government will continue to protect the legal rights of
Taiwan compatriots.
</P>
<P>
"I believe that China will enter the 21st century with a
new outlook, with a new and younger CPC leadership and with
professional knowledge," said a journalist from Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
He expressed his best wishes for both Hong Kong and the
motherland.  
</P>
