<HEADLINE> CPC Congress's Guideline Supported by Non-Communist People </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 30 (Xinhua) -- Leaders of China's
non-Communist parties, the All-China Federation of Industry and
Commerce and figures without party affiliation held a forum here
today to voice their support for the guidelines of the 15th
National Congress of the Communist Party of China.
</P>
<P>
They said that they fully support the congress's report,
various resolutions and the new leading collective with CPC
General Secretary Jiang Zemin at its core.
</P>
<P>
They said that they will closely rally around the CPC Central
Committee with Jiang at its core, adhere to and work toward the
betterment of the system of multi-Party cooperation and political
consultation under the leadership of the CPC, and make new
contributions to the realization of the goals set by the congress.
</P>
<P>
"It is a glorious tradition and political orientation for us to
firmly and unshakably honor the CPC leadership and follow the road
of building socialism with Chinese characteristics," said Ding Shixun,
Chairman of the Central Committee of China Democratic League.
</P>
<P>
Cheng Siwei, chairman of the Central Committee of China
Democratic National Construction Association, said the congress
report is the guideline for the non-Communist parties to follow as
they move into the future.
</P>
<P>
Some of them vowed to unite all the people with Chinese origin at
home and abroad to push ahead the reunification course of the
motherland and to rejuvenate China.
</P>
<P>
They maintained that the basic principles in the primary stage
of socialism will be used to draw plans for the non-Communist
parties to participate in government and political affairs and
play the role of democratic supervision.
</P>
<P>
The leaders also vowed to contribute more to the development of
the country's economy, trade, science, culture and other sectors.
</P>
<P>
China has eight non-Communist parties, namely Jiu San
(September 3) Society, Taiwan Democratic Self-Government League,
Revolutionary Committee of the Chinese Kuomintang, China
Association for Promoting Democracy, China Democratic National
Construction Association, China Democratic League, Chinese
Peasants and Workers Democratic Party, and China Zhi Gong Party
(Public Interest Party).
</P>
<P>
CPC General Secretary Jiang Zemin yesterday attended a forum
held by non-Communist people to mark the success of the congress
which was convened here from September 12 to 18. Jiang made an
important speech at the meeting.  
</P>
</TEXT>
