<HEADLINE> ADB Gives Loans to Indonesia, Mongolia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, September 30 (Xinhua) -- The Asian Development Bank
(ADB) today approved a 100 million U.S. dollar loan to help three
major ports in Indonesia improve their infrastructures.
</P>
<P>
The project will rehabilitate and expand the container, general
cargo and passenger facilities at the ports of Belawan in North
Sumatra, Banjarmasin in South Kalimantan and Balikpapan in East
Kalimantan, the ADB said in a news release.
</P>
<P>
The Manila-based bank also approved a loan of 6.8 million U.S.
dollars to help Mongolia improve water supply and sanitation
services.
</P>
<P>
About 125,000 people will benefit from the Provincial Towns
Basic Urban Services Project which will provide better health and
living conditions for poor people living in traditional Mongolian
tents in the informal settlements of five provincial capitals.
</P>
</TEXT>
