<HEADLINE> Chinese Vice-Premier Meets Friendship Award Winners </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 29 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-Premier Li
Lanqing met with the 45 foreign experts who have won this year's
"Friendship Award" here today.
</P>
<P>
Vice-Premier Li, on behalf of the Chinese Government,
congratulated the winners and expressed his thanks to all the
foreign experts working in China for the contributions they have
made to the country's economic development, science, technology
and culture.
</P>
<P>
