<HEADLINE> Preparation for Macao's Return in Full Swing: Official </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, September 30 (Xinhua) -- The preparatory work for the
return of Macao is in full swing and good order, a senior Chinese
official stationed here announced today.
</P>
<P>
Wang Qiren, director of the Xinhua News Agency Macao Branch,
made the remarks to more than 1,200 guests and celebrities at a
banquet marking the 48th anniversary of the founding of the
People's Republic of China.
</P>
<P>
"Macao's return to the embrace of its motherland in 1999 marks
another important step forward in the course of national
reunification (following the return of Hong Kong)," he said. "The
preparatory work for the return of Macao is being carried out
vigorously and in good order."
</P>
<P>
The Basic Law of Macao is being made known to more people, and
the major issues of transition like the localization of civil
service, the localization of law and the use of Chinese as
official language are all being resolved with great efforts, the
director pointed out.
</P>
<P>
In addition, he said, social and economic development in Macao
is gaining momentum, and the broad masses of Macao compatriots are
also making active preparations for the establishment of the Macao
Special Administrative Region.
</P>
<P>
"In general, Macao will have a stable transition," he stressed.
</P>
<P>
Macao Governor Vasco Rocha Vieira said in a speech at today's
gathering that Macao is making great efforts for the coming of a
"new historic era."
</P>
<P>
He highly praised China's contributions to world peace and the
harmonious co-existence of world nations, adding that it is also
playing an increasingly important role in world economic
relations.
</P>
<P>
The governor said that China's fast economic growth and great
future potential will be a "beneficial factor" for Macao.
</P>
</TEXT>
