<HEADLINE> Wu Yi Stresses Cooperation with Cote d'Ivoire </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 30 (Xinhua) -- Wu Yi, Chinese minister of
foreign trade and economic cooperation, today emphasized the
importance of economic and trade co-operation with Cote d'Ivoire.
</P>
<P>
Wu noted that China encourages domestic enterprises to
establish joint ventures to jointly tap the country's natural
resources.
</P>
<P>
During a meeting with Cote d'Ivoire Planning and Industrial
Development Minister Ahoua n'doli Theophile and his party, Wu said
that bilateral economic and trade cooperation has undergone rapid
growth over recent years because of concerted efforts on the part
of both countries.
</P>
<P>
Wu said that the economies of the two countries are highly
complementary and pointed to the broad sphere and vast potential
for further economic and trade cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show the bilateral trade volume registered a record
high of 62.2 million US dollars in 1996, with the figure for the
first half of this year standing at 64.2 million US dollars, up
105 percent on last year's same period.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese government attaches great importance to economic
and technological cooperation with Cote d'Ivoire and is ready to
jointly explore new cooperative channels and fields, Wu said.
</P>
<P>
Minister Theophile said the government of Cote d'Ivoire
underlined its economic and trade cooperation with China, and
noted that the rapid growth in the bilateral trade volume over the
past few years represents an excellent start in that direction.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, Theophile expressed the hope that more Chinese
enterprises will establish operations in Cote d'Ivoire, and added
that the government of his country will spare no effort to provide
easy accesses. 
</P>
