<HEADLINE> Australian Dollar Closes Firmer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, September 30 (Xinhua) -- The Australian dollar closed
slightly higher today against the US currency in Sydney.
</P>
<P>
The Australian dollar ended at 71.97 US cents from 71.87 US
cents yesterday.
</P>
<P>
Traders said today that the travel allowance scandal
surrounding the federal government over the past few days
continues to weigh on the Australian dollar.
</P>
<P>
"The further it blows up, the more seriously offshore investors
are seeing and thinking about it," said Stuart Moore, St George
Bank foreign exchange manager.
</P>
<P>
The so-called travelgate affair last week saw three government
ministers and two senior advisers to the prime minister resign,
and traders said offshore market participants are keenly watching
developments.
</P>
<P>
The Australian dollar closed at 87.21 yen, from 87.16, and at
1.2681 marks, from 1.2616.  
</P>
