<HEADLINE> Chinese President Meets Canadian Guests </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 30 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin
met here today with former Canadian Prime Minister Pierre Elliot
Trudeau and a delegation from the board of governors of the Bank
of Montreal, led by chairman and CEO Matthew Barret.
</P>
<P>
President Jiang described Trudeau as "an old friend of the
Chinese people," who made active contributions to the
establishment and steady development of Sino-Canadian diplomatic
relations.
</P>
<P>
Jiang welcomed the fact that the Bank of Montreal is holding
its board of governors meeting in China and said that the gesture
will help promote the economic cooperation and trade ties between
China and Canada.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese president expressed hope that the bank will play a
greater role in the development of Sino-Canadian relations.
</P>
<P>
