Barret told President Jiang that members of the board of
governors have personally witnessed the monumental changes in
China, and noted that the bank will further expand cooperation
with the country.
</P>
<P>
This marks the first time in its 180-year history that the
board of governors of the Bank of Montreal has held their meeting
in a country outside North America.
</P>
<P>
The board is composed of high-level managers from leading
companies in Canada's forestry, metallurgical, mining,
petrochemical and aviation industries and banking business, as
well as various other sectors. 
</P>
</TEXT>
