<HEADLINE> Nigeria Plans 8 New Rail Lines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, September 30 (Xinhua) -- Nigeria is to build eight new
railway lines across the country to improve its railway services, the
official New Nigerian newspaper reported today.
</P>
<P>
Chief Gregory Ilukwe, the sole Administrator of the Nigerian
Railway Corporation was quoted as saying at a recent workshop in Jos
that the new lines proposed include a fast line from the capital Abuja
to Kaduna and another from Port Harcourt to Onne.
</P>
<P>
Others are Minna to Abuja, Katsina to Kano, Ajaokuta to Warri,
Ajaokuta to Otukpo, a east-to-west line and a route to run through the
Mambilla.
</P>
<P>
Nigeria currently has over 3,000 kilometers of railway lines which
are at a bad shape and being rehabilitated by a Chinese firm. 
</P>
