<BODY>
<HEADLINE> S. Leone Junta Vows to Defend Ports </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, September 30 (Xinhua) -- The military junta in Sierra
Leone has warned it was ready to defend the ports in the capital
Freetown if the West African Peacekeeping Force (ECOMOG) tried to
attack them.
</P>
<P>
a report reaching here quoted a statement of the junta on
Monday as saying that it would react "positively" if thet ECOMOG
force attempts "to take over two major ports as well as other
mini ports" along the entire coast.
</P>
<P>
The statement is seen as a response to ECOMOG Field Commander
Max Khobe who declared on Sunday that the naval wing of his unit
"will intervene in full force to enforce sanctions and embargo
mandated by the Economic Community of West African States
(ECOWAS)".
</P>
<P>
Economic santions and embargo were approved by ECOWAS at its
summit last month as a means to force the junta to return power
the legitimate government it ousted in the May 25 coup.
</P>
<P>
Khobe, who did not specify when intervention would take place,
said "The naval boast will police the length and breadth of
Sierra Leone's territorial waters to make sure that even canoes
and trawlers don't dodge the ECOMOG net."
</P>
<P>
"We are taking over from the air and infantry wings of ECOMOG
and the naval ships will now carry out most of the military
operations effected by the ECOMOG jets," he added.
</P>
<P>
According to observers, if ECOMOG follows through on the
statement, it could lead to an imminent clash between ECOMOG
forces and the Sierra Leone army, which by all indications would
be bloody.
</P>
<P>
Several clashes have been reported since the embargo was
enforced, with ships at the freetown ports accused of unloading
armes and ammunition attacked by ECOMOG planes.
</P>
<P>
The junta has deployed troops with anti-aircraft equipment at
the main commerical port in the east of Freetown, where it
alleged ECOMOG air raids had killed dozens of innocent civilians.
</P>
<P>
The other port, the government wharf, is in the central
business district which is the base of Sierra Leone's small naval
wing. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
