<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Uganda Supports Global Move to Abolish </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, September 30 (Xinhua) -- Uganda has stopped the
manufacture, import and use of landmines in support of the
global move to abolish anti-personnel mines, local daily
The New Vision reported today.
</P>
<P>
A press release issued from the office of Uganda's permanent
representative to the UN in New York was quoted as saying that
Uganda supports the global move to abolish anti-personnel mines
and has already dismantled a factory for manufacturing mines.
</P>
<P>
Eriya Kategaya, Uganda's Minister of Foreign Affairs said his
country welcomes the results of the recently concluded Oslo
Agreement on the landmines, according to the press release.
</P>
<P>
Uganda also hopes the Oslo process will lead to disarmament
negotiations leading to the complete elimination of nuclear and
other weapons of mass destruction, said the paper. 
</P>
</TEXT>
