<HEADLINE> Sixty-seven Civilians Massacred in Algeria </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, September 30 (Xinhua) -- Sixty-seven civilians were
slaughtered in Algeria in three separate massacres reportedly
committed by the Islamic extremists Sunday and Monday.
</P>
<P>
From Sunday night to Monday morning, 48 people were killed by a
group of armed men near Blida to the south of Algiers, reports
from Algeria said today.
</P>
<P>
Ten workers were killed Sunday night in a construction site in
the district of Puits des Zouaves located at Algiers's highland
area of Bouzarea, while five members of a same family were
slaughtered with axes and saber in Bainem, in the western suburb
of Algiers, said the press reports.
</P>
<P>
Four other people of another family were killed Monday in the
full daytime in Sidi Youcef near Beni Messous, also located at the
highland area of Algiers, where 60 people were massacred in
August. 
</P>
</TEXT>
