<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hungarian Economy Improves in First Seven Months </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUDAPEST, September 29 (Xinhua) -- The Hungarian economy has
improved after its industrial production increased by 7.9 percent
and industrial products exports by 29 percent in the first seven
months of this year over the same period of last year.
</P>
<P>
Exports of industrial products in the period occupied 39
percent of the country's total manufactured goods sales.
</P>
<P>
The agricultural sector was also doing fine. Although the heads of
livestock and fruits output declined, bread grains production was
higher in the months compared with the corresponding period of
last year.
</P>
<P>
In the seven months, Hungary's export volume grew 22 percent
while imports dropped 21 percent, earning a net income for the
first time in years.
</P>
<P>
It is estimated that Hungary's foreign trade growth rate
this year will be several times that of the gross national product
(GNP).
</P>
<P>
Along with the economic improvements, financial condition is
also turning for the better. Deficit in international balance
of payment was reduced by 200 million dollars to 764 million
dollars in the period.
</P>
<P>
By the end of June, Hungary's gross foreign debts totaled 25.1
billion dollars, 2.5 billion dollars less than that of six months
before.
</P>
<P>
The net foreign debts also went down by 800 million dollars to
13.4 billion dollars in the same period. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
