<HEADLINE> Russia Will Never Provide Arms to Taiwan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, September 29 (Xinhua) -- A senior Russian diplomat said
today that Russia would never provide arms to Taiwan in any form,
Itar-Tass News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Leonid Moiseyev, in charge of the Asia-Pacific region in
the Russian foreign ministry, made the remarks in response to a
Taiwan's United Daily News report that said some Russian arms
dealers had expressed willingness to provide Su-37 fighters to
Taiwan as "trainers".
</P>
<P>
He made it clear that Russia would never sell military
technology to Taiwan, adding that deals of this kind are
prohibited in Russia. He stressed that there is only one China in
this world, and Taiwan is an inalienable part of it. 
</P>
