<HEADLINE> Maldivian President Warns Against Global Warming </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, September 30 (Xinhua) -- Maldivian President Maumoon
Abdul Gayoom warned against global warming at the
Intergovernmental Panel on Climate Change (IPCC) which met in the
Maldivian capital of Male lately, according to news reaching here
today.
</P>
<P>
Gayoom told the 200 scientists and experts who attended the
gathering that if the international community did not stop global
warming with a sense of urgency the Maldives and many low-lying
nations would have to face a dismal and alarming future.
</P>
<P>
The main economic activities of the country are fishing and
tourism, both of which depend on the natural environment.
</P>
<P>
The Maldives has taken several measures to protect its fragile
environment, including building coastal defenses, banning coral
mining and protecting endangered species.
</P>
<P>
However, the president expressed disappointment that not enough
had been done internationally to protect and preserve the
environment. 
</P>
