<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sichuan's New Nature Reserve for Giant Panda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, September 30 (Xinhua) -- China's 25th nature reserve
for giant pandas is under construction in southwest China's
Sichuan Province.
</P>
<P>
The Longxi-Hongkou Nature Reserve, which covers 357 sq km, is
located in northwestern Dujiangyan, a city under the jurisdiction
of Chengdu.
</P>
<P>
The nature reserve is home to 2,500 plant species and 500
types of vertebrates, including endangered species such as the
giant panda and snub-nosed monkey.
</P>
<P>
The reserve, along with other reserves such as Wolong,
Fengtongzhai and Huanglongsi, will form an extensive network
offering effective protection for some 1,000 giant pandas
currently living in their natural habitat. 
</P>
</TEXT>
