<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970930.0201 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Black Box of Indonesia's Ill-fated Plane Not Yet Found </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, September 30 (Xinhua) -- The black box of the
ill-fated Garuda Indonesia Airbus A-300 which crashed in North
Sumatra last Friday has not yet been found, an official said.
</P>
<P>
Head of the Provincial Office of the Ministry of Transportation
Aswin Effendi Harahap said Monday in Medan, capital of the North
Sumatra province, that up to 16:00 local time, the rescue team had
not yet found the flight data (FDC) and voice cockpit recorders
(VCB) which could help officials determine the cause of the crash,
reports reaching here today said.
</P>
<P>
The ill-fated Airbus was flying from Jakarta to Medan when it
crashed at Buah Nabar village, Sibolangit district, some 40
kilometers from Medan on September 26, killing all 222 passengers
and 12 crew on board.
</P>
<P>
Official sources said that at least 14 foreigners were among
the 234 people killed in the tragedy. They are two Britons, two
Americans, six Japanese, a Malaysian and an Australian.
</P>
<P>
The accident was feared to have been caused by the haze coming
from raging forest fires on Sumatra Island.  
</P>
</TEXT>
