<HEADLINE> Chinese, Nepalese Enterprises Join Hands in Trade Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 30 (Xinhua) -- Chinese and Nepalese
enterprises inked nine letters of intent in the second meeting of
the China-Nepal Non-governmental Economic Cooperation Forum
concluded here on Monday, according to today's China Daily.
</P>
<P>
According to the report, Nanjing Seek Group, Beijing Vacuum
Flask Industrial Co. and other six Chinese enterprises will export
small generators, vacuum flasks, polyester fiber, CT scanners and
cashmere to Nepal and establish joint ventures.
</P>
<P>
Tianjin Qite Group also signed a letter of intent with the
Nepal Trading Corp. to jointly construct an international airport
in the country.
</P>
<P>
The two-day forum attracted dozens of Chinese private
entrepreneurs and 22 Nepalese business representatives.
</P>
<P>
The successful forum has helped increase cooperation between
the two country's entrepreneurs, intellectuals and academicians,
and is also an effective way to reduce the present trade
imbalance, which favors China, and promote bilateral economic
cooperation, said Pradeeep Shrestha, vice-president of the
Federation of Nepalese Chambers of Commerce and Industry.
</P>
<P>
The forum is a brand new and significant vehicle for the
promotion of bilateral economic links, said Zhang Xuwu,
vice-chairman of the All-China Federation of Industry and Commerce.
</P>
<P>
The first meeting of the forum was held in Nepal last year,
when the two sides decided to make it an annual event. 
</P>
</TEXT>
