<HEADLINE> Drug Baron Turns Himself in to Colombian Government </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTA FE DE BOGOTA, September 29 (Xinhua) -- A drug lord most
wanted by the Colombian police turned himself in at the chief
prosecutor's office here Monday.
</P>
<P>
Orlando Henao Montoya, 44, was the reputed head of the
so-called Norte del Valle drug cartel and was believed to be the
heir apparent of the jailed leaders of the Cali drug cartel.
</P>
<P>
He was investigated for at least two drug-related charges,
including illicit enrichment and money laundering.
</P>
<P>
Henao's lawyer was quoted as saying that the purpose of Henao's
surrender was to clear his name. 
