<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> U.S. to Withdraw First Military Base From Panama </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PANAMA CITY, September 29 (Xinhua) -- The United States will
return to Panama Wednesday a military base it has occupied for 75
years in this Central American country, Panamanian authorities
said today.
</P>
<P>
The Albrook air base, located five kilometers from the capital,
will be the first U.S. wide-ranging military facility in the
Pacific to be returned to Panama.
</P>
<P>
Under the 1977 Torrijos-Carter accords, the U.S. should hand
over the Panama Canal to the control of the Panamanian government
and withdraw all its military presence from there by the end of
the century.
</P>
<P>
A key U.S. military base in Latin America, Albrook was a battle
facility from 1920 to 1961. It became the headquarters of the
Inter-American Air Force Academy in 1943 and had trained 30,000
specialized troops for Latin American countries before it was
turned into a settlement area for U.S. militarymen in 1992.
</P>
<P>
On December 20, 1989, Albrook was one of the vital centers for
U.S. invasion of Panama to overthrow the Noriega government.
</P>
<P>
In September 1955, U.S. troops retreated from Davis and Espinar
bases in the coastal province of Colon, 70 kilometers west of the
capital.
</P>
<P>
Last Friday, the U.S. South Command, settled in Panama since
1920, moved to Miami, Florida. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970930.0209 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Reforming State-owned Enterprises in Tianjin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, September 30 (Xinhua) -- Tianjin, a key industrial
city in north China, will expand the reforms in state-owned
enterprises by adopting modern enterprise system by the end of the
century.
</P>
<P>
According to Mou Huaishan, director of Tianjin Municipal
Economic Commission in charge of state-owned industrial
enterprises, the city plans to raise three billion yuan by listing
these companies on the stock market, said
</P>
<P>
Some of these enterprises in Tianjin have been listed on the
Hong Kong stock market, and other state-owned companies will be
listed on the Tokyo stock market this year.
</P>
<P>
Mou said that the reform of state-owned enterprises has
developed rapidly in Tianjin. In the first seven months of this
year, 48 state-owned enterprises were merged, combined and the
number will rise to 80 by the end of the year.
</P>
<P>
With the use of capital, Tianjin has been able to organize a
group of large inter-regional enterprises so as to improve the
competitiveness of the state-owned enterprises.
</P>
<P>
The municipality will also offer more flexible policies to
small state-owned enterprises and for use of both foreign capital
and state assets. There are now as many as 780 projects involving
co-operation between state-owned enterprises and foreign
businesses in Tianjin.
</P>
<P>
Thirteen state-owned enterprises in Tianjin will be allowed to
declare bankruptcy this year, and the government plans to
re-employ 170,000 laid-off workers in 1997.
</P>
<P>
Mou says that 116 state-owned enterprises in Tianjin are in the
midst of the modern enterprise reform. Twelve are joint-stock
companies, 35 are limited liability companies, and 50 are
state-owned companies.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
