<HEADLINE> Singaporean Insurancer Supports Financial Education </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 30 (Xinhua) -- Singapore's oldest insurance
underwritter on Monday signed agreements in Beijing to
support financial education in China, according to today's China
Daily.
</P>
<P>
The Great Eastern Life Assurance Co. Ltd. and the Graduate
School of the People's Bank of China, the country's central bank,
agreed that the Singaporean side will offer 900,000 (108,000 US
dollars) to set up the Lecture Fund and the Financial Books Fund.
</P>
<P>
The Lecture Fund will invite two or three overseas financial
experts to lecture graduate students annually from 1997 through
2000. The Financial Books Fund will mainly support the publication
of financial theses and books.
</P>
<P>
Ng Sin Keh, chief representative of the company's Shanghai
office, said that the establishment of the funds showed the
company's determination to contribute to China, in which it is
seeking to gain market shares.
</P>
<P>
The company opened its first representative office in Shanghai
in April, anticipating the opening of more offices in other major
Chinese cities, including Beijing. The company also hopes for a
license to operate in China, he said.
</P>
<P>
He said the Chinese market, with its great potential, will play
a key role in the company's global strategy.  
</P>
