<BODY>
<HEADLINE> U.S. to Join Hands With Russia on Nuclear Disarmament </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VIENNA, September 29 (Xinhua) -- The United States Energy
Secretary Federico Pena said today his country will continue to
join hands with Russia in cutting down their nuclear weaponry.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the 40th annual conference of the International
Atomic Energy Agency (IAEA), Pena said the U.S. will put 52,000
kilograms of nuclear materials under international supervision.
</P>
<P>
Pena also praised Russia for its move to put radioactive
material from its nuclear warheads under the supervision of the
world's nuclear watchdog agency.
</P>
<P>
The 106-member IAEA acts both as the U.N. watchdog on
preventing the spread of nuclear weapons and the promoter of its
peaceful use. 
</P>
</TEXT>
