<HEADLINE> Argentine Explorers to Retrieve Treasure From Sunk Galleon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, September 29 (Xinhua) -- A group of Argentine
explorers and divers are trying to retrieve a gold load worth 1
billion U.S. dollars from a galleon sunk off the southern coast
more than two centuries ago.
</P>
<P>
Javier Donatty, chief of the exploring team, said historic
records indicated that the bound-for-Peru galleon was carrying
gold and silver ingots from Uruguay when it sank on January
10, 1765.
</P>
<P>
It has since lain on sea floor near the coast of the Mitre
Peninsula, south of Tierra del Fuego, he said. 
</P>
