<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Russian Population Declines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, September 29 (Xinhua) -- Russia's total population
declined to 147.2 million on August 1, 1997, the Interfax news
agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
The agency, quoting the figures released by the Russian
National Statistics Committee, said that 757,200 babies were born
in the first six months of this year while 1.211 million people
died in the period.
</P>
<P>
The population dropped by 453,800 in the period.
</P>
<P>
The birth rate in the first half of this year decreased three
percent and the death rate went down five percent, compared with
the corresponding period of last year.
</P>
<P>
The big killers were diseases in the blood vessel system and
traffic mishaps, responsible for 55 percent and 13.2 percent of
the total deaths respectively. 
</P>
</TEXT>
