<TEXT>
<P>
SANTIAGO, September 29 (Xinhua) -- Chile's World Cup hopes
suffered a bitter blow Monday when striker Ivan Zamorano was ruled
out of next month's crucial clash with Peru due to a new injury.
</P>
<P>
A Chilean soccer official said that Zamorano, who has scored 12
of his team's 25 goals in the World Cup qualifying competitions,
sustained an injury in a training session with his Italian club
Internazionale earlier on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Zamorano had just recovered from an injury that kept him out of
their last two games which saw Chile go down 1-0 away to Uruguay
and lose 2-1 at home to Argentina.
</P>
<P>
Chile, fifth in the South American World Cup qualifying group
with 19 points from 14 games, still have a chance to book the
fourth and last ticket for France if they defeat Peru in Santiago
on October 12.
</P>
<P>
Colombia, Argentina and Paraguay have already taken up three of
the places in the nine-team group. 
