<DOCNO> XIE19970930.0242 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Californian Forest Fire Destroys 100 Homes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, September 29 (Xinhua) -- A wildfire that started in
northern California Saturday destroyed up to 100 homes and
buildings and forced some 1,500 residents to flee homes.
</P>
<P>
The blaze, sparked by a motor home's generator, burned about
5,800 acres (2,355 hectares) of mountainous terrain in the heavily
wooded Sierra Nevada by early Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Some 1,500 residents in Oregon House and nearby Dobbins were
forced to evacuate the rural area. Hundreds were staying at packed
schools in nearby Brownsville and will not be allowed home for at
least two days.
</P>
<P>
Some 1,140 firefighters were fighting the blaze, aided by air
tankers, helicopters and bulldozers.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, another blaze sparked Saturday night in the
foothills about 117 kilometers north near the town of Ponderosa
Skyranch, had charred about 1,000 acres (about 400 hectares). The
blaze was 50 percent contained. No homes had been destroyed in the
fire.
</P>
<P>
A third fire that burned 1,600 acres (650 hectares) in central
California was also contained Sunday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
