<DOCNO> XIE19970930.0245 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> UN Postpones Enactment of Travel Sanctions on UNITA </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, September 29 (Xinhua) -- The U.N. Security
Council today decided to postpone until October 30, 1997 the
enactment of measures restricting the travel of senior officials
of the National Union for the Total Independence of Angola (UNITA)
and adult members of their families and sealing UNITA offices.
</P>
<P>
Those other measures including prohibition of the flight of
aircraft by or for UNITA, and the supply of aircraft or their
components to UNITA, and the insurance, engineering and servicing
of UNITA aircraft were to be imposed Tuesday, September 30, unless
the council was informed by the secretary-General that UNITA has
taken concrete and irreversible steps to comply with the council
demands.
</P>
<P>
The council affirmed its readiness to review the imposition of
those measures and to consider the imposition of additional
measures if UNITA failed to meet its demands.
</P>
<P>
The council stressed the need for UNITA to comply fully with
all obligations set out by the council's resolutions. The required
actions include the demilitarization of all of its forces, the
transformation of the radio station Vorgan into a non-partisan
broadcasting facility and full cooperation in the normalization of
state administration throughout Angola. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
