<DOCNO> XIE19970930.0252 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Turkish PM in Bonn to Seek Support for EU Membership Bid </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, September 29 (Xinhua) -- Prime Minister Mesut Yilmaz of
Turkey said here today that it is unjust to exclude Turkey from
the enlargement process of the European Union.
</P>
<P>
Yilmaz, who began today a three-day visit to Germany, made the
remark in a speech to Germany's umbrella organization of chambers
of commerce DIHT in Bonn this evening. He is scheduled to meet
German Chancellor Helmut Kohl Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
In an article carried by the German Frankfurter Allgemeine
newspaper today, Yilmaz said that given its military, economic and
political status, Turkey was an "indispensable element" of the EU
policy in regions like the Middle East, the Balkans and Central
Asia.
</P>
<P>
However, he also noted that Ankara believed that some
artificial barriers were being set up to keep Turkey out of the
EU.
</P>
<P>
"Turkey expects Germany's support in its efforts to become a
full EU member," Yilmaz said.
</P>
<P>
German Foreign Minister Klaus Kinkel said earlier this month
that Turkey should first resolve its dispute with Greece over the
divided island of Cyprus and human rights concerns stemming from
its conflicts with separatist Kurds. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
